body:
@NazIrizarry Thanks for the contribution! I can certainly understand how this is a useful feature to have. The only concern that I have is that I don't believe that "Run Once" fits as a Scheduling Strategy. Instead, I think the user should have the ability to right-click on a Processor and click "Run Once" and the Processor would then immediately run, regardless of what the scheduling strategy is (though if configured to run on Primary Node only, it should still only run on Primary Node).

Thanks
-Mark
